a0=a1.jm("1. Introduction","Welcome to the Volcan Vision Client Supply Chain Management App (\u201cApp\u201d).\nThis App is developed and owned by Volcan Vision and Automation Pvt. Ltd. (\u201cCompany\u201d, \u201cWe\u201d, \u201cOur\u201d, \u201cUs\u201d).\n\nBy using this App, you (\u201cClient\u201d, \u201cUser\u201d) agree to these Terms & Conditions (\u201cTerms\u201d).\nIf you do not agree, please stop using the App immediately.")
s=a1.jm("2. Restricted Use & Eligibility","\u2022 This App is exclusively created for a specific client of Volcan Vision and is not for public use.\n\u2022 Only users authorized by the Client are permitted to access and operate the App.\n\u2022 The Client is fully responsible for managing authorized users and preventing unauthorized access.")
r=a1.jm("3. Account Access & Security","\u2022 Users must provide accurate information during account creation or onboarding.\n\u2022 The Client must ensure that login credentials are kept confidential.\n\u2022 The Company may suspend or terminate access if misuse, unauthorized activity, or security concerns are detected.")
q=a1.jm("4. Intellectual Property Rights","All elements of the App\u2014including software code, architecture, UI/UX, workflows, designs, and content\u2014are the sole intellectual property of Volcan Vision and Automation Pvt. Ltd.\n\nThe Client is granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the App for internal business operations only.\nThe Client must not:\n  - Copy, modify, or redistribute the App\n  - Reverse engineer or attempt to extract the underlying source code\n  - Create derivative or competing products\n  - Share the App or its components with third parties\n\nAll rights not expressly granted remain with the Company.")
p=a1.jm("5. Data Policy & Privacy","The App may collect and store data necessary for the Client\u2019s internal operations, including:\n\n\u2022 Order, production, inventory, supply chain, and expense data\n\u2022 Basic user information\n\u2022 Uploaded documents or files\n\u2022 Technical logs and usage metadata\n\nData Ownership\n\u2022 All operational data belongs to the Client.\n\u2022 The Company may only access data for:\n  - Technical support\n  - Bug fixing\n  - Maintenance\n  - Feature enhancements requested by the Client\n\nData Protection\n\u2022 Data is handled and stored following industry-standard security practices.\n\u2022 Data is never sold or shared with third parties except as required by law.\n\nAny pre-existing NDA or Data Processing Agreement between the Client and the Company takes precedence over these Terms.")
o=a1.jm("6. Third-Party Services","The App may rely on third-party platforms essential for its functionality, including but not limited to Supabase, Firebase, GitHub.\n\nThese services operate under their own terms and privacy policies.\nThe Company is not liable for:\n\u2022 Downtime or disruptions caused by third-party providers\n\u2022 Data loss or performance issues due to external service outages\n\u2022 Policy or technical changes introduced by these service providers\n\nThe Client acknowledges that the App depends partially on the availability and performance of these third-party systems.")
n=a1.jm("7. Software Updates","\u2022 All updates, patches, and enhancements will be planned, discussed, and coordinated directly with the Client.\n\u2022 Updates may include improvements, bug fixes, or new modules.\n\u2022 No unannounced automatic updates will be pushed unless explicitly agreed.")
m=a1.jm("8. Prohibited Use","The Client and authorized users must not:\n\n\u2022 Use the App for illegal or unauthorized purposes\n\u2022 Attempt to bypass, hack, or exploit the App\u2019s security systems\n\u2022 Conduct penetration testing without the Company\u2019s written approval\n\u2022 Share internal business data externally without authorization\n\u2022 Upload malicious files or engage in harmful activities\n\u2022 Use the App beyond the operational scope agreed with the Company\n\nMisuse may result in immediate suspension or termination of access.")
l=a1.jm("9. Warranty Disclaimer","The App is provided on an \u201cas-is\u201d and \u201cas-available\u201d basis.\n\nThe Company does not guarantee:\n\u2022 Uninterrupted access\n\u2022 Error-free performance\n\u2022 Compatibility with third-party hardware or software not approved by the Company\n\u2022 Accuracy of data entered by the Client\u2019s users\n\nThe Company is not responsible for operational decisions made based on the data provided through the App.")
k=a1.jm("10. Limitation of Liability","To the maximum extent permitted by law, the Company is not liable for:\n\n\u2022 Financial losses or business disruptions\n\u2022 Supply chain delays or production issues\n\u2022 Incorrect entries or data provided by users\n\u2022 Data loss caused by third-party services\n\u2022 Any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages\n\nThe Client is solely responsible for validating decisions based on the App\u2019s information.")
j=a1.jm("11. Termination","The Company may suspend or terminate App access under the following circumstances:\n\n\u2022 Violation of these Terms\n\u2022 Unauthorized access attempts\n\u2022 Security threats\n\u2022 Expiry or termination of the service agreement\n\nThe Client may request account deletion or data removal at any time.")
a1=a1.jm("12. Governing Law","These Terms shall be governed by and interpreted according to the laws of Gurgaon, Haryana, India.\nAny disputes shall fall under the exclusive jurisdiction of courts located in Gurgaon, Haryana.")
